Faculty profile




Alfred  KobsaProfessor EmeritusDEGREE:Ph.D. 1985, University of Vienna and Technical University of Vienna, AustriaRESEARCH AREAS: Computer-Supported Cooperative WorkHuman Computer InteractionMedical InformaticsUbiquitous ComputingRESEARCH INTERESTS: Dr. Kobsa's research lies in the areas of user modeling and personalized systems (with applications in the areas of information environments, expert finders, and user interfaces for disabled and elderly people), privacy, and in information visualization. He is the editor of "User Modeling and User-Adapted Interaction: The Journal of Personalization Research", edited several books and authored numerous publications in the areas of user-adaptive systems, human-computer interaction and knowledge representation.
CONTACT INFORMATION:

